                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d828">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">493.11/2260: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to the
                        Ambassador in Japan</hi> (<persName type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">Grew</hi>
                    </persName>)</head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1939-04-20T19:00:00-05:00"
                            >April 20, 1939—7 p.m.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>104. Peiping’s despatch 1954, March 10,<note n="73" xml:id="d828fn73">Not
                        printed.</note> Tsinghua University. The Department suggests that in your
                    discretion you renew your representations of February 3, 1938.<note n="73"
                        xml:id="d828fn75">Not printed.</note> You may wish to review the nature and
                    extent of the American interest in the University as set forth in the
                    Department’s 28, January 27, 1938, 7 p.m., to Peiping<note n="73"
                        xml:id="d828fn74">Not printed.</note> and to express the hope that there
                    will be issued to the Japanese military authorities in Peiping such instructions
                    as may be required to rectify the unsatisfactory situation described in
                    Peiping’s despatch under reference.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Hull</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
